<% page_title('MIME Types') -%>

<p>Mack application supports all standard MIME types out of the box.</p>

<p>If necessary, you can register new MIME types for your application by modifying the mime_types.rb file located in {APP_DIR}/config/initializers folder.</p>

<p>Here's an example on how to register a new MIME type:</p>

<% code do %>
  Mack::Utils::MimeTypes.register(:my_new_type, "app/my_new_type")
<% end -%>